From: lichenggang <lichenggang@uniontech.com>
Date: Mon, 31 Mar 2026 16:30:00 +0800
Subject: Add sw_64 (Sunway) architecture support

The sw_64 (Sunway) architecture is a Chinese processor architecture
used in high-performance computing and servers. This patch adds
sw_64 to the list of recognized CPU types in config.sub and adds
detection support in config.guess, enabling proper build configuration
on sw_64 systems.

Without this patch, configuring packages that use gnulib's config.sub
for sw_64-linux-gnu targets fails with:
  "Invalid configuration 'sw_64-unknown-linux-gnu': machine 'sw_64-unknown' not recognized"

Signed-off-by: lichenggang <lichenggang@uniontech.com>
---
 build-aux/config.guess | 4 ++++
 build-aux/config.sub   | 1 +
 2 files changed, 5 insertions(+)

--- gnulib-20250303.orig/build-aux/config.guess
+++ gnulib-20250303/build-aux/config.guess
@@ -1024,6 +1024,10 @@ EOF
 	if test "$?" = 0 ; then LIBC=gnulibc1 ; fi
 	GUESS=$UNAME_MACHINE-unknown-linux-$LIBC
 	;;
+	sw_64:Linux:*:* | sw64:Linux:*:*)
+	UNAME_MACHINE=sw_64
+	GUESS=$UNAME_MACHINE-unknown-linux-$LIBC
+	;;
     arc:Linux:*:* | arceb:Linux:*:* | arc32:Linux:*:* | arc64:Linux:*:*)
 	GUESS=$UNAME_MACHINE-unknown-linux-$LIBC
 	;;


diff --git a/build-aux/config.sub b/build-aux/config.sub
index fc5419ae..3b3c8d12 100644
--- a/build-aux/config.sub
+++ b/build-aux/config.sub
@@ -1430,6 +1430,7 @@ case $cpu-$vendor in
 			| sparcv9b \
 			| sparcv9v \
 			| spu \
+			| sw_64 \
 			| sv1 \
 			| sx* \
 			| tahoe \
